<DocsPageTitle Path="Helpers/Utilities/Display">
    Blazorise Display Utilities
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Show, hide, or switch display modes at each breakpoint with a fluent display builder.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Display utilities let you control visibility and layout directly from components, keeping responsive rules close to the markup and consistent across providers.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    How it works
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Set the <Code>Display</Code> parameter on any component and chain display values with breakpoints, for example <Code>Display.None.Block.OnFullHD</Code>.
    When you use <Code>Display.Flex</Code> or <Code>Display.InlineFlex</Code>, you can also chain direction helpers like <Code>Row</Code> and <Code>Column</Code>.
</DocsPageParagraph>

